        Creates an HTTP entity to be sent to fetch Reporting API auth token.
        Parameters:
        apiUrl - Url of the Reporting API
        apiVersion - Version of the Reporting API
        username - Username of the user
        password - Password of the user
        clientVersion - Version of the client device
        uniqueId - String identifier that client device registers with AW to identify itself
        clientNickname - Client device nickname
        sslContext - An optional SSL context which can be used for certificate based authentication.
        requestInfo - Optional parameter, can be null. Use RequestInformation object here to supply additional information about the request, including request headers, params information about the request if necessary.
        Returns:
        UrlEncodedFormEntity object represents HTTP entity to be sent to fetch auth token
        Throws:
        ReportingAPISDKException
